{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=~"},{"type":"text","text":" operator to match a string against a regular expression pattern. The operator returns a boolean value indicating whether the string matches the pattern."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let email = \"john.doe@example.com\"","if email =~ \"[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}\" {","    print(\"Valid email\")","} else {","    print(\"Invalid email\")","}"]},{"anchor":"Extracting-Matches","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Extracting Matches"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"matches(for:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method allows you to extract all matches in a string for a given regular expression pattern. It returns an array of strings representing the matched substrings."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let sentence = \"The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog\"","let matches = sentence.matches(for: \"\\\\b\\\\w{5}\\\\b\")","print(matches) \/\/ [\"quick\", \"brown\"]"]},{"anchor":"Replacing-Matches","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Replacing Matches"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"replace(regex:with:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method replaces occurrences of a regular expression pattern in a string with the specified replacement text. It returns a new string with the matched substrings replaced."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let sentence = \"Hello, world!\"","let newSentence = sentence.replace(regex: \"\\\\b\\\\w{5}\\\\b\", with: \"Swift\")","print(newSentence) \/\/ \"Hello, Swift!\""]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/aputils\/regex"],"trait